{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside.","Place flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, liqueur, eggs and egg yolk into mixing bowl and knead <nobr>1 min\/<\/nobr>.","Add almonds and mix <nobr>40 sec\/<\/nobr>. Transfer to prepared baking sheet; dough should be thick and sticky at this point—do not add more flour! Shape dough into 3 logs (12 in. x 1¼ in.). Place 2 inches apart on prepared baking sheet. Bake 30 minutes (350°F) or until golden brown. The baked dough will still be soft, allow to cool 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300°F.","Place baked logs on a cutting board and diagonally cut each into 12 slices using a sharp knife. Place slices, cut side down, on baking sheet and bake a further 15 minutes (300°F). Allow to cool completely before storing in an airtight container."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["9 oz all-purpose flour","7 oz sugar","1 pinch salt","2 tsp baking powder","½ oz anise-flavored liqueur","2 large eggs","1 egg yolk, from large egg","5 ½ oz almonds, with skin"]}],"id":"r113840","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-eruPLEkMuAk\/XZWrLHP2kyI\/AAAAAAAAfjQ\/4QaNejM0_yET2B9Na5BU_lOE1wNoPYT_ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ddGdMt4LUhFMu1mR.png","title":"Almond Biscotti","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"2 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"8 g","calories":"236 kJ \/ 56 kcal"},"usefulItems":"airtight container, baking sheet, parchment paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Ideal to serve with coffee or tea.","In Tuscan tradition, Biscotti are served with the sweet dessert wine \"Vin Santo\"."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","1h 50m","36 pieces"]}